==English==
===Etymology===
From [[glyco-]] (meaning, "a sugar"), + -ide (similar to [[glucoside]]). (1925-1930).
===Noun===
'''glycoside'''
#A molecule in which a [[sugar]] group is bound to a non-sugar group by a nitrogen or oxygen atom.  Glycosides yield a sugar after undergoing [[hydrolysis]].
